
# View full conexions
netstat -a

# Only TCP
netstat -at

# Only UDP
netstat -au

# List Sockets 
netstat -l

# Sow PID of process how use the conexion
netstat -p -at

# Routing table
netstat -r

# A lot of thing
netstat -napl

## Binary to use without install
https://github.com/andrew-d/static-binaries/blob/master/binaries/linux/x86_64/ncat